Attention MIDDLE & HIGH SCHOOL Families:
The Parshall Schools use AIMSWeb to place students into their proper reading and math academic levels which helps the teaching staff provide interventions to all our students.
To meet the needs of our students we ask that students take this assessment under the supervision of the teaching staff. Testing will take between 30 minutes to an hour.
We would like to schedule a time for your child to come to the school and take the AIMSWeb assessment. We have created spaced seating with shield protectors. Student areas will be sanitized before and after assessments. Chromebooks will be provided which will be sanitized before and after. Face masks will be provided if needed.
Please select the date and time that works best for you.

From Coach Spotted Horse:
PHS girls, grades 7-12. Monday, Aug 17th will be the first day of volleyball practice🏐🏐 @ 5:00pm @ the high school. Spread the word to every girl you know who is interested in joining. Must have physical to practice. From my understanding, if you have a physical on file from last year, there is a waiver form you can fill out (you can contact the office to get) & you won't require a new one. If you DO NOT have a physical from last year, you will need one in order to participate in practice. I will also have them post day & time on the school page too hopefully. See you all on Monday, get excited for our first season in that beautiful new gym😬

post_text:
Mr Hamm's summer thought for all of you...

Mindful Minute for the day-
A thought my sister wrote several years ago and I say every night,
**Please instill within me a feeling of peace and take my fears away and replace them with love so that I’m not looking at the past with worry, regret or longing nor to the future with worry, dread, anxiety and impatience but instead am happy to be in the moment, being a part of all that is.

Fitness Challenge for Day: Keep Moving and Loving the Outside!

post_text:
There are 2 open seats on the School Board and we have 3 candidates. The election is on Tuesday, June 16, 2020. The election is open to all voters in the Parshall School District.

This years elections will be held by Absentee Ballot. You can pick-up the Asentee/Mail Ballot Application at Parshall Food Pride, and the Parshall Post Office. You can also download the application on the school website.

The completed applications, need to be returned so a voter ballot can be mailed to you.

The ballot needs to be dropped in the ballot box at the high school or post marked no later than Monday, June 15, 2020 by 5:00pm.

The ballot box will be located in the foyer of the high school.

Class of 2020 & Family,

Governor Burgum has approved North Dakota schools to have graduation on school grounds. Administration has decided to have our first graduation in the new high school gymnasium on Sunday, May 24th @ 4 pm. There are social distancing rules we need to follow. Staying six feet away, hand shakes or hugs, & staying home if you are sick are a few we will enforce.

We will be get out information as soon as possible

Stay safe & healthy!

WE MISS YOU! 💜💜

ND Department of Public Instruction
May 4 at 10:28 AM ·

What is to be done about high school graduation? The governor and the superintendent of public instruction are working on guidance for holding high school graduation ceremonies. All options are being considered. This guidance should be issued by Friday, May 8. The governor’s March 22 executive order is still in effect. It closes all public and nonpublic school facilities to students until further notice.

Full STEAM Ahead updated their cover photo.

With everything that's been going on, there is a dedicated group of individuals who's passion is to feed our kids. They come in early in the mornings to make sure breakfasts are made and packed and lunches are delicious and ready to be brought to you curbside.

Their love for cooking is contagious and their smiles well, are they brighten our days. They are often times overlooked when accolades are being handed out. They don't mind, because they like to work behind the scenes to make sure everybody's belly is full. ❤❤

THANK YOU PARSHALL SCHOOL DISTRICT KITCHEN STAFF for feeding our kiddos and community during these troubled times. We appreciate you more than you'll ever know!!

post_text:
This evening Governor Burgum announced that the State of North Dakota K-12 schools be closed for 1 week. The closure will begin Monday, March 16th. This will give the State time to best figure out what needs to be done.

UPDATE: We will be providing a breakfast to be picked up from 9:00-9:30am and carry out lunch from noon to 1:00pm for all students only at both the elementary and at the high school. These meals will not be eaten at the schools, as the lunch rooms will be closed.

Here is the link: https://www.kxnet.com/news/health/coronavirus/governor-announces-k-12-closures-for-5-days-in-north-dakota/

post_text: Parshall FFA high 5 to your medals you earned this past weekend!! Parshall Strong!! Way to represent!
shared_text:
Parshall FFA
February 15 at 3:42 PM ·

Parshall FFA represented their Chapter and town well at the Kindred CDEs. Andrew received a Gold ribbon, placing 12th of 98, with an impressive score of 963 points out of a possible 1100. Tyson picked up a Silver ribbon, adding 50 points to his personal best. In the Junior 4-H division, Alyssa Haakenson placed 2nd of 31, achieving a whopping 732 points of 800 possible. Brendan placed 5th with 694 points, and Rebecca placed 18th, picking up a TEAM WIN for Mountrail County! Way to go! As always, thanks to Coach Roger!

post_text:
Hello,

We are asking for your help to keep our bus lane in front of the New High School clear of vehicles. This area is designated as a bus lane for pickup and drop off only. The lane also needs to be kept clear for our first responders (EMS, FIRE, and POLICE) in case of any emergencies. We understand parking is an issue and additional parking is being addressed. Please help us by not parking in front of the new school during the school day or during any events. Thank you very much!

---SRO Sitting Bear

Did you know Parshall High School students have access to FREE Audible books this year? If you are at least 13 years old, you'll get FREE access to hundreds of audio books from the Audible for Schools Library. You'll also get 3 FREE credits each quarter to use on books of your choice! The books in the Audible for Schools Library have captions to follow along with the reading.
To gain access, compete the permission slip in the comments and return it to Ms. Curlee or Mrs. Grubb as soon as possible.

Today we had a special speaker at school. His name is Jeff Yalden and he's a motivational speaker, mentor and a great listener. He met with all of our students, then met with student council, national honor society, and other school student leaders. He then met with individual classes and lastly the staff and faculty. Highly motivating, thought provoking and at times emotional. Ask your student what they walked away with.
This is Jeff talking with the student body and then student leadership. 💜
